8
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:26,618
Truth in the syntactical side is given by a valid proof

9
00:00:26,718 --> 00:00:30,748
in a deductive calculus. We represent this by this relation:

10
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,309
and it means that there is a formal proof of phi from

11
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:39,895
Sigma. Proofs are computational processes which can be visualized by a proof-tree.

12
00:00:40,066 --> 00:00:43,574
Truth in the semantical side is based on Tarki's

13
00:00:43,674 --> 00:00:47,633
definition of truth. Namely that something is true iff

14
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:51,016
it is true in all models. Here this relation:

15
00:00:51,066 --> 00:00:54,007
which is read as Sigma models phi, means that in

16
00:00:54,107 --> 00:00:57,997
every structure where Sigma is satisfied phi is also satisfied.

17
00:00:58,097 --> 00:01:01,671
In other words, there is no structure in the mathemtatical

18
00:01:01,771 --> 00:01:05,281
universe, which satisfies Sigma but does not satisfy phi.

19
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:09,589
For example, if we have an order relation in our vocabulary and Sigma

20
00:01:09,689 --> 00:01:14,624
is the set of sentences expressing that the order relation is transitive, meaning

21
00:01:14,724 --> 00:01:17,359
that for all a, b and c: if a is less than b

22
00:01:17,459 --> 00:01:20,033
and b is less than c then a is less than c,

23
00:01:20,066 --> 00:01:24,067
and irreflexive, meaning that for all a: a is not less than a,

24
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:27,574
and we let phi be the sentence expressing that the order

25
00:01:27,674 --> 00:01:31,053
